A jQuery (1.7.1) plugin that turns an HTML-list into a paged list, showing a chosen number of items from the list per page. There is a parameter with which you can choose which page should be shown initially.

<h3>Sample Markup:</h3>
<ul class=&quot;list&quot;&gt;
	<li>Item 1 of 6</li>
	<li>Item 2 of 6</li>
	<li>Item 3 of 6</li>
	<li>Item 4 of 6</li>
	<li>Item 5 of 6</li>
	<li>Item 6 of 6</li>
</ul>

<h3>Example Usage with Defaults:</h3>
$('.events').listPagination({
	containerClass: 'listpag-container',
	itemsPerPage: 10,
	navigatorClass: 'listpag-navigator',
	navigatorLocation: 'after',
	startPage: 1
});